          <li><strong>Timeline Extension:</strong> Scope changes will extend project timelines accordingly. The original timeline estimates no longer apply.</li>
        </ul>

        <p><strong>Managing Scope Creep:</strong></p>
        <p>Scope creep—the gradual expansion of project requirements—is one of the most common causes of project delays and budget overruns. To avoid scope creep: (a) be thorough in your initial requirements; (b) consolidate feedback from all stakeholders before submitting; (c) avoid "while you're at it" requests; (d) understand that small requests can accumulate quickly; and (e) communicate any concerns about scope early rather than requesting changes piecemeal.</p>

